<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc9d00ff8-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s390h–12h"><num value="390h–12h">§ 390h–12h.</num><heading> El Paso Water Reclamation and Reuse Project</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idc9d00ff9-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s390h–12h/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Authorization</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary, in cooperation with the appropriate State and local authorities, is authorized to participate in the design, planning, and construction of the El Paso Water Reclamation and Reuse Project to reclaim and reuse wastewater in the service area of the El Paso Water Utilities Public Service Board, El Paso, Texas.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idc9d00ffa-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s390h–12h/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Cost share</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Federal share of the cost of a project described in subsection (a) shall not exceed 25 percent of the total cost.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idc9d00ffb-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s390h–12h/c"><num value="c" class="bold">(c)</num><heading class="bold"> Limitation</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall not provide funds for the operation or maintenance of a project described in subsection (a).</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idc9d00ffc-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/pl/102/575/tXVI/s1622">Pub. L. 102–575, title XVI, § 1622</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/104/266/s2/a/2">Pub. L. 104–266, § 2(a)(2)</ref>, <date date="1996-10-09">Oct. 9, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/3292">110 Stat. 3292</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
